---
description: User-facing UI text must stay Russian and dashboard tables must keep stable alignment
globs: Frontend/src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

# UI language and tables

1. All user-facing UI text should be in Russian. Technical codes, machine-readable enums, and backend statuses may stay in English internally.
2. Do not scatter hardcoded fallback strings through components when the shared UI copy layer can own them.
3. If backend returns technical codes, frontend should map them to understandable Russian labels.
4. For dashboard tables, center column headers by default.
5. Center numeric values in table cells and keep text-heavy columns like names, vendor codes, and search phrases left-aligned unless there is a clear reason not to.
6. When adding or changing table cells with numeric values, use an explicit numeric-cell class such as `wb-table-cell--numeric` instead of relying on accidental inheritance.
7. If a table mixes raw WB data and text values, detect numeric cells and center only those values.
